{
  "text": "During previous irradiation of non-axenic cells of the haptophyte E. huxleyi by solar light, it was observed that UVRinduced photosensitized cis-trans isomerisation processes acted not only on monounsaturated fatty acids but also on their oxidation products [CITATION_1] . In the studied sediments, the lack of 9-cis and 10-cis hydroxyacids (arising from oleic acid oxidation) and 11-cis and 12-cis hydroxyacids (arising from cis-vaccenic acid oxidation) previously proposed as potential tracers of the effects of UVR insitu [CITATION_2] suggests that cis-trans isomerisation of monounsaturated fatty acids observed in sediments from the Beaufort Shelf does not result from the involvement of UVR-induced photosensitized processes in the water column.",
